headline: Kraft Heinz Announces Three New Members of Its Board of Directors
summary: PITTSBURGH & CHICAGO, October 22, 2025--The Kraft Heinz Company (Nasdaq: KHC) ("Kraft Heinz" or "the Company") announced today that L. Kevin Cox, Mary Lou Kelley, and Tony Palmer have been appointed to join its Board of Directors ("Board"), effective Oct. 22, 2025.

headline: How Do Profit Pressures and Shifting Taste Trends Shape Kraft Heinz's (KHC) Competitive Edge?
summary: Kraft Heinz is preparing to announce its fiscal third-quarter 2025 earnings, with analysts expecting a double-digit decline in profits and ongoing weak fundamentals amid heightened competition and changing consumer trends. Despite these challenges, analyst skepticism remains high as fundamental concerns about sales declines and margin pressures persist, even as the company invests in product improvements and manufacturing capabilities.
